Three circular arcs of radius 5 units bound the region shown. Arcs $AB$ and $AD$ are quarter-circles, and arc $BCD$ is a semicircle. What is the area, in square units, of the region?

\begin{tikzpicture}[scale=0.8]
% Draw the region bounded by three arcs
% Quarter-circle AB (from A to B, curving left)
\draw (0,-2) arc[start angle=-90, end angle=180, radius=2] -- cycle;
% Point labels
\node[above] at (0,2) {$C$};
\node[left] at (-2,0) {$B$};
\node[right] at (2,0) {$D$};
\node[below] at (0,-2) {$A$};
% Draw the actual figure: semicircle BCD on top, quarter-circles AB and AD below
\draw (-2,0) arc[start angle=180, end angle=0, radius=2]; % semicircle BCD
\draw (-2,0) arc[start angle=90, end angle=0, radius=2]; % quarter-circle from B to A
\draw (2,0) arc[start angle=90, end angle=180, radius=2]; % quarter-circle from D to A
\end{tikzpicture}
